leadingComments.value: eslint-disable

*
   * @typedef {Object} CustomVariable
   * @property {string} name - Name of custom variable
   * @property {string} value - Value of custom variable

*
   * @typedef {Object} App
   * @property {boolean} isMobile - Weather current running environment is mobile device.
   * @property {function(list:CustomVariable[]):void} setCustomVariable - Set custom variable.

*
   * @typedef {function} onStatusChangeCallback
   * @param {boolean} online - Whether current status is online
   * @return {void}

*
   * @typedef {Object} Button
   * @property {string} type - Type of button, possible options are:
   * + 'monitor' - monitor button
   * + 'text' - text button
   * + 'static' - static image button
   * + 'float' - float image button
   * + 'mobile-image' - mobile image button
   * + 'mobile-text' - mobile text button
   * + 'adaptive' - adaptive button
   * @property {number} id - Campaign id of button
   * @property {function():Promise<void,Error>} click - Simulate click behavior, the same as user click on this chat
   * button.
   * @property {function(callback:onStatusChangeCallback):void} onStatusChange - Register callback,
   * which will be notified when status of current campaign changed.

*
   * @typedef {Object} Agent
   * @property {number} id - Uniq of agent
   * @property {string} name - Display name of agent
   * @property {string} avatar - Source of avatar image
   * @property {string} bio - Bio description of agent
   * @property {string} title - Title of agent

*
   * @typedef {Object} Invitation
   * @property {string} type - Type of invitation, possible options are:
   * + 'image' - image invitation
   * + 'adaptive' - adaptive invitation
   * + 'embedded-window' - popup embedded chat window directly
   * + 'mobile' - mobile invitation
    * @property {string} message - Message of current invitation.
  * @property {Agent} agent - Agent info, will only be provided if it's a manual invitation.
  * @property {function():Promise<void,Error>} accept - Accept invitation manually
  * @property {function():Promise<void,Error>} refuse - Refuse invitation manually
  * @property {function(callback:function)} onAccept - Register callback function when invitation is
  * accepted (either by visitor or programatically).
  * @property {function(callback:function)} onRefuse - Register callback function when invitation is
  * refused.

*
   * @typedef {Object} Message
   * @property {string} type - Type of message
   * @property {{type:string,name:string}} sender - Sender of message, possible types of sender are:
   * + 'visitor'
   * + 'agent'
   * + 'system'
   * @property {Date} time - Creating time of this message
   * @property {string|object} content - Detailed content of message

*
   * @typedef {function} MessagesOnChangeCallback
   * @param {Array<Message>} messages - Current version of messages
   * @return {Array<Message>} messages that should be displayed

*
   * @typedef {function} SingleMessageOnChangeCallback
   * @param {Message} message - Current version of message
   * @param {number} index - Index of current message (in messasge list)
   * @param {Array<Message>} messages - The complete message list
   * @return {Message|null|Array<Message>} The transformed message. If `null` is provided, this
   * message will be removed from list; if a list of message is provided, all of them will be rendered
   * in list.

*
   * @typedef {Object} ChatContent
   * @property {function(callback:MessagesOnChangeCallback):void|{type:string,callback:SingleMessageOnChangeCallback}} onChange - Register callback function to
   * transform message in list.  possible message types are:
   * + 'waiting-queue'
   * + 'agent-join'
   * + 'agent-leave'
   * + 'agent-text'
   * + 'visitor-text'
   * + 'end-chat'
   * + ...

*
   * @typedef {Object} Field
   * @property {string} type - Type of field, possible types are:
   * + 'input' - single line input field
   * + 'textarea' - Multiple line input field
   * + 'radiolist' - Group of radio buttons
   * + 'checkbox' - Single checkbox field
   * + 'select' - Dropdown list field
   * + 'checkboxlist' - Group of checkbox
   * + 'file' - Attachment upload field
   * + 'email' - Input field that accept email address
   * + 'ticket' - Input field that accept Comm100 Ticket number
   * + 'department' - Dropdown list that display available department
   * + 'stars' - Field for user to rate the chat (select from 1 to 5 stars by default)
   * + 'custom' - Custom field that display whatever user provide in element property
   * @property {string} name - Label name of field
   * @property {string|number} value - Value of current field
   * @property {boolean} isSystem - Whether the field is system field
   * @property {string} error - Potential error of this field with current value. This error might
   * or might not be displayed, usually it will be displayed after field blur or before form submit.
   * @property {Array<{type:string,name:string}>} options - Possible options of current field, only
   * valid when type is `select`, `radiobox` or `checkbox`.
   * @property {HTMLElement} element - Extended element, only valid when type is `custom`

*
   * @typedef {function} FieldOnChangeCallback
   * @param {Array<Field>} prevFields - Previous version of fields. For initial run, this will be
   * default value.
   * @param {Array<Field>} fields - Current version of fields.
   * @return {Array<Field>} fields that should be displayed.

*
   * @typedef {function} FieldOnClickCallback
   * @param {string} id - Field id.
   * @param {Array<Field>} fields - Current version of fields
   * @return {Array<Field>} fields that should be displayed

*
   * @typedef {Object} FormData
   * @property {string} name
   * @property {string} email
   * @property {string} phone
   * @property {string} company
   * @property {int} ticketId
   * @property {int} departmentId
   * @property {string} productService
   * @property {Array<{name:string,value:string}>} customFields

*
   * @typedef {function} OnSubmitCallback
   * @param {FormData} formData - Current form data.
   * @return {Object} form data that should be submitted.

*
   * @typedef {function} OnErrorCallback
   * @param {Error} error - Occured error.

*
   * @typedef {Object} Form
   * @property {function(callback:FieldOnChangeCallback):Form} onChange - Transform original fields to match
   * situation.
   * @property {function(callback:FieldOnClickCallback):Form} onClick - Transform
   * list of fields on click event of any provided field
   * @property {function(callback:OnSubmitCallback):Form} onSubmit - Transform original submit
   * data, use this API if you would like to provide field data programatically.
   * @property {function(callback:OnErrorCallback):Form} onError - Trigger callback when error
   * occurs. For example, when providing incorrect submit data.
   * @property {function(formData:FormData):Promise<void,Error>} submit - Submit form with provided data.

*
   * @typedef {function} RenderCallback
   * @return {HTMLElement|null} If provides an HTMLElement, original component will not be rendered;
   * if provides null, use original component instead.

*
   * @typedef {function} AttachTabCallback
   * @param {object} param - Parameters used to render tab
   * @return {HTMLElement|null} If `null` is provided, this tab will be hide temporarily; otherwise,
   * HTMLElement will be append to this tab.

*
   * @typedef {object} ExtendedWindow
   * @property {function(tab:string,callback:AttachTabCallback):ExtendedWindow} attachTab -
   * Extends extra window with one more tab.
   * @property {function(tab:?string,param:?object):Promise<void,Error>} show - Display specific
   * extended tab, rendering the tab with given parameters. If none `tab` is provided, it will
   * display default tab if there is any.
   * @property {function():Promise<void,Error>} hide - Hide extra extended window.

*
   * @typedef {Object} ChatWindow
   * @property {number} campaignId - Campaign id
   * @property {function():Promise<void,Error>} minimize - Minimize current chat window
   * @property {function(callback:function):ChatWindow} onMinimize - Register callback which will be
   * called when chat window is minimized.
   * @property {function():Promise<void,Error>} close - Close current chat window
   * @property {function(callback:function):ChatWindow} onClose - Register callback which will
   * be called when chat window is closed
   * @property {function():Promise<void,Error>} endChat - End current chat
   * @property {function(callback:function):ChatWindow} onEndChat - Register callback which will
   * be called when chat is ended
   * @property {function():Promise<void,Error>} restore - Restore current chat window
   * @property {function(callback:function):ChatWindow} onRestore - Register callback which will
   * be called when chat window is restored
   * @property {function(callback:function):ChatWindow} onAgentJoinChat - Register callback which
   * will be called when agent joins the chat. Agent info will be provided.
   * @property {function(type:string,callback:RenderCallback):ChatWindow} onRender -
   * Render customized element. If callback provies an HTMLElement, original component will not be
   * rendered; if provides null, use original component instead.
   *
   * Function also accepts a visitor for multiple callback registration.
   *
   * Possible render types are:
   * + 'prechat.header'
   * + 'prechat.content'
   * + 'prechat.footer'
   * + 'chat.header'
   * + 'chat.content'
   * + 'chat.footer'
   * + 'postchat.header'
   * + 'postchat.content'
   * + 'postchat.footer'
   * + 'offline.header'
   * + 'offline.content'
   * + 'offline.footer'
   * + '*.header'
   * + '*.content'
   * + '*.footer'
   * @property {Form} prechatForm - Useful api to get/set prechat form
   * @property {Form} postchatForm - Useful api to get/set postchat form
   * @property {Form} offlineForm - Useful api to get/set offline message form
   * @property {ChatContent} chatContent - Useful api to get/set chat content
   * @property {ExtendedWindow} extendedWindow - Useful api to get/set extended window

*
 * @property {function(app:App):void} onAppReady - API that will be triggered when live chat app is ready, which is after JavaScript has been
 * downloaded and initialized.
 * @property {function(button:Button):boolean} onButtonWillDisplay - API that will be triggered before certain button is rendered, providing useful API to get/set
 * the button, also provide feature to prevent rendering if necessary. If function returns `false`,
 * it will prevent rendering current button.
 * @property {function(invitation:Invitation):boolean} onInvitationWillDisplay - API that will be triggered before certain invitation is rendered, providing useful API to get/set
 * the invitation, also provide feature to prevent rendering if necessary. If function returns `false`,
 * it will prevent rendering current invitation.
 * @property {function(chatWindow:ChatWindow):boolean} onWindowWillDisplay - API that will be triggered before chat window is rendered, providing useful API to get/set
 * the chat window, also provide feature to prevent rendering if necessary. If function returns `false`,
 * it will prevent rendering current chat window.
 * @property {number} site_id - Site Id
 * @property {function():void} onLiveChatCodeLoaded - API that will be triggered when live chat app is ready, which is after JavaScript has been
 * downloaded and initialized.
 * @property {function():Promise<void,Error>} ban - Ban visitor
 * @property {boolean} dynamic - Whether uses dynamic campaign
 * @property {function(callback:function):Promise<void,Error>} end_chat - End current chat if there is any
 * @property {function(params:{DOMElement:HTMLElement})} onBeforeImageInvitationDipslay - Triggers before image
 * invitation has been displayed.
 * @property {function(params:{DOMElement:HTMLElement})} onAfterImageInvitationDisplay - Triggers after image
 * invitation has been displayed.
 * @property {function} onChatWindowLoadBegin - @deprecated
 * @property {function} onChatWindowLoaded - @deprecated
 * @property {function} onChatWindowStatusChanged - @deprecated (not in used actually)
 * @property {function(event:Event,campaignId:number):Promise<void,Error>} open_chat_window - Open chat window, where `event` can be
 * a regular Event, it's default behavior will be prevented if provided; `campaignId` is the campaign id
 * @property {function} setIfHideChatWindowLoadingAnimation - @deprecated
 * @property {function(ifSkipPrechat:boolean):Promise<void,Erro>} setIfSkipPrechat - Set if skip prechat form.
 * @property {function(fields:Array<{name:string,value:string}>):Promise<void,Error>} setPrechatFields - Set prechat fields
